text: Rennie Harrison was a professional footballer who played once for Huddersfield Town in the Football League in the 1919–20 season. He played as a defender. Harrison was born in 1897 in Burnley, and retired from football in October 1920. ==References== Category:English footballers Category:Association football defenders Category:English Football League players Category:Huddersfield Town A.F.C. players Category:1897 births Category:Year of death missing Category:Sportspeople from Burnley Category:Place of death missing
